ing to design the frame work of the game for me? I want to mimic the feel of FF4 with a menu system and battle system that are identical to FF4. Let me know if you are interested.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcrazykidgaming.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkspirit>DarkSpirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#D15400>(8/22/02 2:29:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Final Fantasy: Call of the Dragon</span><hr size=1> If you are looking for the feel of final fantasy i would advise switching to Rpg Maker 3 as it allows for ff style battles. as fro the feel of the game that could be difficult as it had a certain something that made it difficult. i could try with the storyline <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F7F7F7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/udrakedarken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drake Darken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#D15400>(8/23/02 8:56:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Final Fantasy: Call of the Dragon</span><hr size=1> Oh, I've already got plenty of ideas for the storyline (though suggestions wouldn't hurt.) As for the graphics, I have the game on an emulator. Just pause the game, press the &quot;Print Screen&quot; button, then paste it into paint... It's a great way to, er, borrow graphics.<br>
<br>
What is this RPG Maker 3 you mentioned? Where can I get it, and (more importantly) would I be able convert RPG Maker 2000 games? I'm knee deep into my game, &quot;Shades of Black.&quot; Though RPG Maker 2000 is great in many ways, the battle system is kind of pathetic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcrazykidgaming.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkspirit>DarkSpirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#D15400>(8/23/02 2:38:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Final Fantasy: Call of the Dragon</span><hr size=1> Currently the Rpg Maker 3 is in translation. i believe good all don miguel is doing this one too. im sure you can transfer the all the maps into the rpg maker 3 from rpg mkr 2k. im not actually sure where you can get it from but serahc on google or msn and its sure to be there <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F7F7F7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/usquall1957.showPublicProfile?language=EN>squall1957</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#D15400>(8/25/02 9:59:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Final Fantasy: Call of the Dragon</span><hr size=1> The maker you refer to is Rpgmaker 2003. It is still waiting to be realeased but when it is im sure some 1 will transalate. I have heard that there is a built in game importer to so your rm2k games can probably be transferred. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/udrakedarken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drake Darken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#D15400>(8/26/02 7:07:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Hard Way</span><hr size=1> I could always try to make a FF4 system using just RPGMaker 2000, but that'd take more energy than I'm willing to devote right now. Oh, well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcrazykidgamingfrm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BB